# .env.example
# Copy this file to .env or .env.local and fill in your values.
# DO NOT COMMIT ACTUAL SECRETS (.env or .env.local files are ignored by git)

# Example API URL
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000/api

# Example Public Key
VITE_STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_test_yourkeyhere

# How Vite Handles .env:
#
# * Vite automatically loads variables from .env files in your project root.
# * Files like .env, .env.local, .env.development, .env.production are supported.
# * Crucially: Only variables prefixed with VITE_ (e.g., VITE_API_KEY) are exposed to your client-side code for security reasons.
# * Access them in your React code using import.meta.env.VITE_YOUR_VARIABLE_NAME.
